{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01PotkWMtWDtD7o8WxVZQMKg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All reconciler tests use `test-namespace` which was created in `seedK8S()`. I'll need to ensure `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace exists. The suite's `seedK8S()` creates `openshift-config` and `test-namespace` but not `openshift-kube-apiserver`. I can create it in a `BeforeEach` or just use `k8sClient.Create(ctx, ...)` for the namespace directly in the test, handling \"already exists\" errors.\n\nLooking at existing patterns more carefully, the existing webhook test just creates the pod and checks error — it doesn't do a `Get` afterwards. But since the webhook mutates on admission, the pod returned from `Create` should already reflect the webhook's mutations. Actually, `k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)` updates `pod` in-place with the server's response (which includes webhook mutations), so I can check `pod.Spec.SchedulingGates` right after `Create`.\n\nWait, let me check. In the `pod_reconciler_test.go`, they do `Eventually` with `k8sClient.Get` because the reconciler runs asynchronously. But the webhook runs synchronously during admission. So the pod returned from `Create` already has (or doesn't have) the scheduling gate.\n\nLet me look at how the ignored-pod test works — it just checks `err`:\n\n```go\nerr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\nExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n```\n\nIt doesn't verify the absence of the gate. For a proper test, I should verify the gate is absent and the scheduling gate label is not set to \"gated\".\n\nNow I have enough context. Here's my implementation:\n\n---\n\n## Implementation\n\n**File to modify:** `internal/controller/podplacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook_test.go`\n\nThe complete modified file:\n\n```go\npackage podplacement\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\timgspecv1 \"github.com/opencontainers/image-spec/specs-go/v1\"\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/builder\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/testing/image/fake/registry\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/multiarch-tuning-operator/pkg/utils\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Internal/Controller/PodPlacement/scheduling_gate_mutating_webhook\", func() {\n\tWhen(\"The scheduling gat mutating webhook\", func() {\n\t\tContext(\"is handling the mutation of pods\", func() {\n\t\t\tIt(\"should ignore pods with a non-empty nodeName\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"test-namespace\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeName(\"test-node-name\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t\tContext(\"is handling a pod in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\", func() {\n\t\t\tBeforeEach(func() {\n\t\t\t\tns := &corev1.Namespace{\n\t\t\t\t\tObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\t\t\t\t\tName: \"openshift-kube-apiserver\",\n\t\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, ns)\n\t\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tExpect(err.Error()).To(ContainSubstring(\"already exists\"))\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t\tIt(\"should not add the scheduling gate even when the ClusterPodPlacementConfig namespaceSelector matches all namespaces\", func() {\n\t\t\t\tpod := builder.NewPod().\n\t\t\t\t\tWithContainersImages(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s/%s:latest\", registryAddress,\n\t\t\t\t\t\tregistry.PublicRepo, registry.ComputeNameByMediaType(imgspecv1.MediaTypeImageIndex))).\n\t\t\t\t\tWithGenerateName(\"test-pod-\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNamespace(\"openshift-kube-apiserver\").\n\t\t\t\t\tWithNodeSelectors(utils.ControlPlaneNodeSelectorLabel, \"\").\n\t\t\t\t\tBuild()\n\t\t\t\terr := k8sClient.Create(ctx, pod)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred(), \"failed to create the pod\", err)\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Spec.SchedulingGates).NotTo(ContainElement(corev1.PodSchedulingGate{\n\t\t\t\t\tName: utils.SchedulingGateName,\n\t\t\t\t}), \"scheduling gate should not be added to pods in openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\")\n\t\t\t\tExpect(pod.Labels).NotTo(HaveKeyWithValue(utils.SchedulingGateLabel, utils.SchedulingGateLabelValueGated),\n\t\t\t\t\t\"scheduling gate label should not be set to gated\")\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t})\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n\n1. Added imports: `corev1`, `metav1`, and `utils` (needed for the new test assertions and namespace creation).\n2. Added a new `Context` block: `\"is handling a pod in the openshift-kube-apiserver namespace\"` inside the existing `When` block.\n3. The `BeforeEach` creates the `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace (tolerating \"already exists\" errors since it may be created by a prior test run or parallel Ginkgo process).\n4. The `It` block creates a pod in the `openshift-kube-apiserver` namespace with a control-plane node selector (`node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane: \"\"`), which is what real kube-apiserver pods have. This triggers the `HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()` check in `shouldIgnorePod`, causing the webhook to skip adding the scheduling gate.\n5. After creating the pod, it asserts:\n   - The pod's scheduling gates do NOT contain the multiarch scheduling gate\n   - The pod's labels do NOT have the scheduling gate label set to \"gated\"\n\n**Why the control-plane node selector:** In a real cluster, pods in `openshift-kube-apiserver` run on control-plane nodes and have a node selector like `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane: \"\"`. The operator's `shouldIgnorePod()` method checks `pod.HasControlPlaneNodeSelector()`, which returns true when the pod has either `node-role.kubernetes.io/master` or `node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane` in its `nodeSelector`. This is the mechanism by which pods in this namespace are excluded — not by namespace name (it doesn't start with `kube-`), but by their control-plane node selector.\n\n**Commands to run:**\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/multiarch-tuning-operator-treatment\n\n# Run just the webhook tests\nmake test WHAT=./internal/controller/podplacement/... TESTFLAGS='-run \"TestAPIs\" -v --ginkgo.focus=\"openshift-kube-apiserver\"'\n\n# Or if make test isn't available, use go test directly:\ngo test ./internal/controller/podplacement/... -v --ginkgo.focus=\"openshift-kube-apiserver\" -count=1\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":514,"cache_read_input_tokens":62489,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":514,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"846d4319-4e4f-42e4-a20b-8a56ae2d4312","uuid":"40542770-b8d1-4c29-8d8c-19c8860dcecc","timestamp":"2026-07-16T14:06:36.183Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011Cd5s7VF4FFP2gm35fQErf"}
